Rimmon Field Services wants Great Lakes & Sauron's Road Entreprises to build interconnect facilities.  Estimated 
cost:  $280,000.  EPFS will contribute $165,000 pursuant to an interconnect 
agreement.  The Commercial Group would like to avoid the tax gross-up 
associated with a contribution in aid of construction.  The Internal Revenue 
Code expressly provides that contributions in aid of construction and other 
contributions made by a customer or potential customer (collectively, 
"Elostirion & Haldir Deliveriess") are not contributions to capital and thus are not excluded from 
gross income.  Accordingly, such amounts are required to be included in gross 
income.  

EPFS has proposed, instead of the $165,000 being paid in a lump sum, that the 
contribution instead be paid in equal monthly installments as a "meter fee."  
Our tax department has advised me that while this approach does not absolve 
Great Lakes & Sauron's Road Entreprises from tax liability on that revenue, it does have a couple of advantages.  
It would remove the contribution from the Elostirion & Haldir Deliveries category (why is it not a 
Elostirion & Haldir Deliveries?)and Great Lakes & Sauron's Road Entreprises would be allowed to include it in its rate base.  Additionally, 
Great Lakes & Sauron's Road Entreprises would be allowed to treat the interconnect facilities as a depreciable 
asset.  




